    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hardhat compatible, sure, but... Hardhat Network needs to know what hardfork to use to execute in the context of a given historical block, and it looks like your config is missing that information.  The [default config](https://github.com/nomiclabs/hardhat/blob/db1f4a5d64005e16a9d495e58c45781035f6a533/packages/hardhat-core/src/internal/core/config/default-config.ts#L35) contains [hardfork activation histories for the well-known Ethereum public networks](https://github.com/nomiclabs/hardhat/blob/db1f4a5d64005e16a9d495e58c45781035f6a533/packages/hardhat-core/src/internal/core/config/default-config.ts#L35), but that's it (no Avalanche).\r\n\r\nHave you seen [the \"Using a custom hardfork history\" section of the Mainnet Forking guide](https://hardhat.org/hardhat-network/guides/mainnet-forking.html#using-a-custom-hardfork-history)?",
